    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-09-10T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-09-10T11:00:00-05:00" n="850"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d850">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">836.48 1930 Hurricane/40: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in the Dominican Republic</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Curtis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-09-10T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 10, 1930—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>48. Your September 9, 11 a.m.,<note n="19" xml:id="d850fn19">Not printed.</note>
                    and September 9, noon. The Department is most reluctant to have a marine
                    detachment sent to Santo Domingo and will consent only if you consider their
                    presence absolutely necessary. In any event the Department would have to have a
                    formal definite request from the Dominican Government to you. If you are sure
                    that it is necessary you may explain to the President that this Government is
                    most anxious to help him but <pb facs="0833" n="735" xml:id="pg_735"/> that the
                    sending of marines will create misunderstanding in other countries. Even if you
                    want them we may not agree to send them.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
